  "prompt": "How do you pronounce \"Hamfer\u00f0\"?",
  "response": "\"Hamfer\u00f0\" is pronounced approximately as **\"HAM-ferth\"** in English. Here\u2019s a breakdown:\n\n- **Ham** sounds like the word \"ham\" (as in the meat).\n- **fer\u00f0** sounds like \"ferth,\" where the \"\u00f0\" (an Icelandic letter called \"eth\") is pronounced like a soft \"th\" as in \"this.\"\n\nIn Icelandic, the stress is on the first syllable, so it\u2019s **HAM-ferth**. Icelanders would pronounce it with a rolling \"r\" and a very clear \"th\" sound, so it might sound slightly different than the anglicized version.",
